Bhawesh Agrawal
Hey guys! mr penguin is here to explain! The joke here starts out with the common situation a lot of us are in right now which is online schooling. Throughout this meme there’s a bunch of different people and what they do during online school. The first part shows your teacher being unable to unmute the class so the image next to that is them being super upset. The next part shows you telling your teacher to press “Alt +F4.” Now someone doing this would result in the current window on the computer being closed which would exit the zoom so you have an evil expression on your face. The next one shows the kid with a loud microphone, after that there’s the teachers dog in the background barking up a storm which further distracts the class. There’s then the kid who’s trying to learn looking annoyed which totally makes sense because it’s very tough to learn on online class. We then see your FBI agent seemingly looking entertained which is because watching an online class take place as an outsider would be hilarious. Lastly we see the kid with slow internet just loading. So this meme is here to represent how strange online classes truly are. and hey, if you’ve already read this far, you might as well drop a follow! I explain memes like this all the time :) @penguin_explains2

Circular to the Parents 
(Classes IX & XI)

Dear Parents/Guardians,

This is to inform you that the Final Examination - 2020/21 of classes IX & XI will be held from 26th April 2021(Monday). The time table and online examination related information will be given to the students by their respective class teachers.

Kindly note that the students are appearing Final Examination through virtual mode (online).

The students whose dues are not cleared will not avail the link to appear in the Final Examination.

So, all the parents are kindly requested to clear all the pending dues (if any) by 25th April 2021 without fail.

Kindly contact school account section if you have any query between 8am to 3pm.

Looking forward to your kind co-operation.

Thanking you. 

Dr Bhubaneswari Rao

29th March 2021

Circular To The Parents
(Classes Nursery to XII)

Dear Parents/Guardians,

This is to inform you that the Ministry of Education, Science & Technology has issued a circular calling, to close the school from 30th March 2021 to 2nd April 2021 due to hazardous Smog . Smog can give rise to serious health issues especially among the children.

Such, the school will remain closed on the above mentioned dates.

All the students from Nursery to 9 &11, (except the Board Bound Classes), will attend the online classes from their homes, on the said dates.

The Board bound students of Grade 10 & 12 will utilise the break for Self Study in co-ordination with their teachers.

Kindly, note that the school will resume from 4th April 2021(Sunday) as usual.

Parents are kindly requested to restrain all out door activities of their children till the smog is prevalent.

Thanking You,

Dr Bhubaneswari Rao
(Principal)

The sound board operates by the principle of forced vibration. The string gently vibrates the board, and despite their differences in size and composition, makes the board vibrate at exactly the same frequency. This produces the same sound as the string alone, differing only in timbre.

Out of elements 34X17 and 40X18, the element 34X17 is chemically more reactive. ... With a very heavy heart we are informing you all that we have lost one of our most promising student of Grade IX Master Simon Oli at the age of 15 on 19th December, 2020 due to cardiac arrest.

His untimely death has devastated all of us. It will surely take some days for all of us to recover from this shock. 

Hence, to mourn the sudden death of our beloved student, the school will remain closed on 23rd December 2020 (Wednesday) and all the online classes will be cancelled on this day.

Kindly note that the online classes will resume from 24th December 2020 (Thursday) as usual.

Thanking You,

Dr Bhubaneswari Rao
(Principal)

24th December 2020
Circular To The Parents
( Grade-Nursery to VIII)

Dear Parents/Guardians,

This is to inform you that the online classes for (Grade Nursery to VIII) will be cancelled from 25th December 2020 to 1st January 2021 as preparatory leave for the upcoming 2nd periodic examination.

Kindly note that the online classes will resume from 3rd January 2021 (Sunday) as usual for Grade 5 to 8.
And 4th January (Monday) for Grade Nursery to IV.

Thanking You,

Dr Bhubaneswari Rao
(Principal)
